HEADWORD: Glomerule
<hw>Glom"er*ule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. fr. L.
<ets>glomus</ets> ball.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A head or dense cluster of
flowers, formed by condensation of a cyme, as in the flowering
dogwood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A glomerulus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glomerulus</ent>⟦br⟧
